    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02351.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">45. Wall Street<ptr target="loc.02351_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1890-10-20">Oct 20, 90</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Whitman,</salute>
            </opener>  
            <p>I recd the printed speech, proposed&#8212;think it too short. Better leave it all to
                your feeling at the time.<ptr target="loc.02351_n3"/></p>
            <p>I do hope that we shall have a good time. Have some fear that Philadelphia
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02351.002.jpg" type="verso"/>
                is a little slow<ptr target="loc.04697_n2"/>&#8212;but hope for the best.</p>
            <p>In any event, I want the whole thing to suit you. It is something to be appreciated.
                "Not to be understood strikes a man more dead than a great reckoning in a little
                room"<ptr target="loc.02351_n2"/>&#8212;</p>
            <p>You must take
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.02351.003.jpg" type="recto"/>
            good care of yourself&#8212;get in good trim physically, so that my speech will do
                you no bodily harm.&#8212;</p>
            <p>"May the Lord take a liking to you&#8212;but not too soon"</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours always</salute> 
                <signed>R.G. Ingersoll</signed>
            </closer> 
